OL,3,CChancellor's local Labour party urges
OL,4,Cher to abandon welfare cuts
OL,6,FThe CLP also acknowledged welfare
OL,7,Freform is important, but urged the
OL,8,FGovernment to "focus on reducing the
OL,9,Ftaper" - the rate at which benefits
OL,10,Ffall off once someone has found work.
OL,12,FThe local Labour group resolved to
OL,13,Fwrite to both Chancellor Ms Reeves and
OL,14,FWork and Pensions Secretary Liz
OL,15,FKendall to "articulate our proposed
OL,16,Fcuts to disability benefits - whether
OL,17,Fby reducing rates, implementing higher
OL,18,Fthresholds, poor quality assessments
OL,19,For increased conditionality - as soon
OL,20,Fas possible".
