OL,3,CChancellor's local Labour party urges
OL,4,Cher to abandon welfare cuts
OL,6,FThe opposition comes as the government
OL,7,Fappears at risk of a major rebellion
OL,8,Ffrom its backbenchers over the plans.
OL,10,FThe Chancellor's team, approached for
OL,11,Fcomment, pointed to her previous
OL,12,Fmessages to Labour MPs on the welfare
OL,13,Fcut proposals.
OL,15,FWhen asked last week what her message
OL,16,Fto concerned Labour backbenchers was,
OL,17,FMs Reeves said: "I don't think
OL,18,Fanybody, including Labour MPs and
OL,19,Fmembers, think that the current
OL,20,Fwelfare system created by the
OL,21,FConservative Party is working today.
